&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Abstract and Contents: Critical Problems cannot be solved by routine thinking. With the rapid changes in technology, conventional methods used to solve problems are no longer effective. There is a need to develop new ways of thinking in order to design better solutions, services and experiences that solve our current problems. Innovation is the process of creating and implementing a new idea. It is the process of taking useful ideas and converting them into useful products; services or processes or methods of operation. These useful ideas are the result of creativity, which is the prerequisite for innovation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.interaction-design.org/literature/topics/design-thinking&quot;&gt;Design Thinking&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;steps in with a bold newly systematised and non-linear human-centred approach. This will help us radically change how we go about exploring problems and creating solutions to those problems. This workshop will aim at providing a systematic approach to Innovation and Design thinking. People from Industry, Entrepreneurs, Students and Faculty are encouraged to attend this workshop. The workshop content is as follows.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
